I got one question: If you pull say a green, blue and yellow(red?), which mob is it best to take down first. The greens die fastest, but the reds dish the most damage?? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Usually I sic my pet on tanks target, and if there is a weak secondary mob that still does much damage to the tank, I burn it down. Of course especially casters. HeeHee, nothing more fun that casting at same time as the Wizard, and that Orc Priest just topples over from 70% health.<br>
<br>
Secondly, dont totally dump the AE idea. It is a weapon which we can use, and even if the risk is HIGH, so is the reward. Mana efficiency is the key word. For example, if you fight 2 equal mobs, and one at low health, an AE will kill the low, harm the other, and your mana efficiency will be larger than casting a DD?<br>
